The paper deals with optimization problems related to facility location and routing, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and optimization (cs.DS, cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and robotics (cs.RO). The use of linear programming techniques also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the subfield of mathematical programming (cs.MS). However, since the focus of the paper is on facility location and routing, we consider the aforementioned sub-categories to be more likely.
